Six suspected drug peddlers have been arrested by the Katsina State command of the Nigeria Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) in connection with a seized trailer loaded withÂ  24,000 bottles of cough syrup with codeine. The NDLEA named two of the suspects: Christian Chukwuma, alleged to be a salesman, and Obiora Chukwuma who is the manager of Sunglow Equity Nigeria Ltd. Speaking, the state commander, Maryam Sani, said the arrest was made at a warehouse in Dutsenreme area of Funtua in collaboration with a joint taskforce. She said the consignment was moving from Onitsha to Funtua. Christian Chukwuma who spoke, said he was only a messenger who was called to help offload the commodity.